      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2017-05-19</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2018-05-03T17:57:53Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Mortgage Fairness Act of 2017 </b></p> <p>This bill amends the Truth in Lending Act to revise the definition of&nbsp;"points and fees," for purposes of determining whether a mortgage is a "high-cost mortgage," to: (1)&nbsp;exclude compensation taken into account in setting the interest rate and for which the consumer was not separately charged, and (2) include compensation paid by a consumer or creditor to an individual employed by or contracting with a mortgage originator. (A high-cost mortgage designation restricts the terms of&nbsp;a loan and requires a lender to make certain disclosures to the borrower.) </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
